The Senate has confirmed Muhammad Usman as the Commissioner for National Population Commission (NPC). The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Usman’s confirmation followed consideration and adoption of a report of the Senate Committee on National Identity and National Population. Chairman of the Committee, Sen. Saidu Alkali, while presenting the report, said the nominee possessed the requisite qualifications, integrity, leadership qualities and comportment to discharge his responsibilities. According to him, Usman’s appointment satisfies the requirements of Section 154(1) of the Constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria, 1999 (as amended). Usman was the Registrar of Federal University of Technology, Minna, between 2007 and 2012 and a member of the African Council on Communication Education. He is also a member of the Association of Nigerian University Professional Administrators (ANUPA) and Nigeria Institute of Management (NIM). Usman is also a Fellow of the Institute of Corporate Administration and the Nigerian Institute of Public Relations (NIPR).